Helper functions to visualize intermarriage rates. The first draws two lines, one for observed and one for adjusted, and has optional arguments to group by a variable (e.g.Â \(\texttt{Province}\)), and exclude the low power decades of 1921-1930 and 1931-1940. The second computes the difference and plots it. Both draw 95% confidence intervals.

plot_intermarriage <- function(data, title, group_var = NULL, exclude_decade = TRUE) {
    names(data) <- gsub("National_", "", names(data))
    names(data) <- gsub("Province_", "", names(data))
    names(data) <- gsub("Const_", "", names(data))

    if (exclude_decade) {
        data <- data %>% filter(!DecadeMarried %in% c("1921-1930", "1931-1940", "1941-1950"))
    }
    
    if (!is.null(group_var)) {
        data <- data %>% mutate(group = .data[[group_var]])
    } else {
        data <- data %>% mutate(group = 1)
    }
    
    data <- data %>%
        mutate(
            Observed_CI_lower = Observed_mean - 1.96 * Observed_SE,
            Observed_CI_upper = Observed_mean + 1.96 * Observed_SE,
            Adjusted_CI_lower = Adjusted_mean - 1.96 * Adjusted_SE,
            Adjusted_CI_upper = Adjusted_mean + 1.96 * Adjusted_SE
        )
    
    ggplot(data) +
        geom_line(aes(x = DecadeMarried, y = Observed_mean, group = group, color = "Observed")) +
        geom_ribbon(aes(x = DecadeMarried, ymin = Observed_CI_lower, ymax = Observed_CI_upper, group = group, fill = "Observed"), alpha = 0.1) +
        geom_line(aes(x = DecadeMarried, y = Adjusted_mean, group = group, color = "Controlling for Exposure")) +
        geom_ribbon(aes(x = DecadeMarried, ymin = Adjusted_CI_lower, ymax = Adjusted_CI_upper, group = group, fill = "Controlling for Exposure"), alpha = 0.1) +
        scale_color_manual(values = c("Observed" = "red", "Controlling for Exposure" = "blue")) +
        scale_fill_manual(values = c("Observed" = "red", "Controlling for Exposure" = "blue")) +
        theme_pubclean() +
        theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, vjust = 1, hjust = 1)) +
        labs(title = title, color = "", fill = "", x = "Decade Married", y = "Value")
}

plot_intermarriage_difference <- function(data, title, group_var = NULL, exclude_decade = TRUE) {
    names(data) <- gsub("National_", "", names(data))
    names(data) <- gsub("Province_", "", names(data))
    names(data) <- gsub("Const_", "", names(data))

    if (exclude_decade) {
        data <- data %>% filter(!DecadeMarried %in% c("1921-1930", "1931-1940", "1941-1950"))
    }
    
    if (!is.null(group_var)) {
        data <- data %>% mutate(group = .data[[group_var]])
    } else {
        data <- data %>% mutate(group = 1)
    }
    
    data <- data %>%
        mutate(
            Difference = Adjusted_mean - Observed_mean,
            Difference_SE = sqrt(Adjusted_SE^2 + Observed_SE^2),
            CI_lower = Difference - 1.96 * Difference_SE,
            CI_upper = Difference + 1.96 * Difference_SE
        )
    
    ggplot(data) +
        geom_line(aes(x = DecadeMarried, y = Difference, group = group, color = as.factor(group))) +
        geom_ribbon(aes(x = DecadeMarried, ymin = CI_lower, ymax = CI_upper, group = group, fill = as.factor(group)), alpha = 0.1) +
        scale_color_discrete(name = group_var) +
        scale_fill_discrete(name = group_var) +
        theme_pubclean() +
        theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, vjust = 1, hjust = 1)) +
        labs(title = title, color = "", x = "Decade Married", y = "Difference (Controlling for Exposure - Observed)")
}

Process constituency-level data, storing the observed, expected, and adjusted values. Also finds the population with the number of rows. Process is repeated for ethnic blocks. NAs are removed because some denominators are zero (aka no exposure due to small samples) â all data has been scanned for missingness.

process_constituency_ethnic <- function(data) {
    const_intermarriage_ethnic <- data %>%
        select(Const, District, Province, Ethnicity, EthnicOutmarriage, DecadeMarried) %>%
        left_join(y = ethnic_proportions, by = join_by(Const, Ethnicity)) %>%
        group_by(Const, District, Province, Ethnicity, Proportion, DecadeMarried) %>%
        reframe(Observed = mean(EthnicOutmarriage), n = n()) %>%
        mutate(Expectation = 1 - Proportion) %>%
        mutate(Adjusted = Observed / Expectation) %>%
        ungroup()

    const_ethnic <- const_intermarriage_ethnic %>%
        group_by(Const, District, Province, DecadeMarried) %>%
        summarise(
            Const_Population = sum(n),
            Const_Adjusted_mean = sum(Adjusted * Proportion) / sum(Proportion, na.rm = TRUE),
            Const_Observed_mean = sum(Observed * Proportion) / sum(Proportion, na.rm = TRUE),
            Const_Expectation_mean = sum(Expectation * Proportion) / sum(Proportion, na.rm = TRUE),
            Const_Adjusted_SE = sqrt(sum(Const_Population * (Adjusted - Const_Adjusted_mean)^2, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)) / sqrt(sum(Const_Population)),
            Const_Observed_SE = sqrt(sum(Const_Population * (Observed - Const_Observed_mean)^2, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)) / sqrt(sum(Const_Population)),
            Const_Expectation_SE = sqrt(sum(Const_Population * (Expectation - Const_Expectation_mean)^2, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)) / sqrt(sum(Const_Population))
        ) %>%
        ungroup()
    
    return(const_ethnic)
}

process_constituency_block <- function(data) {
    const_intermarriage_block <- data %>%
        select(Const, District, Province, EthnicBlock, BlockOutmarriage, DecadeMarried) %>%
        left_join(y = ethnic_block_proportions, by = join_by(Const, EthnicBlock)) %>%
        group_by(Const, District, Province, EthnicBlock, Proportion, DecadeMarried) %>%
        reframe(Observed = mean(BlockOutmarriage), n = n()) %>%
        mutate(Expectation = 1 - Proportion) %>%
        mutate(Adjusted = Observed / Expectation) %>%
        ungroup()

    const_block <- const_intermarriage_block %>%
        group_by(Const, District, Province, DecadeMarried) %>%
        summarise(
            Const_Population = sum(n),
            Const_Adjusted_mean = sum(Adjusted * Proportion) / sum(Proportion, na.rm = TRUE),
            Const_Observed_mean = sum(Observed * Proportion) / sum(Proportion, na.rm = TRUE),
            Const_Expectation_mean = sum(Expectation * Proportion) / sum(Proportion, na.rm = TRUE),
            Const_Adjusted_SE = sqrt(sum(Const_Population * (Adjusted - Const_Adjusted_mean)^2, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)) / sqrt(sum(Const_Population)),
            Const_Observed_SE = sqrt(sum(Const_Population * (Observed - Const_Observed_mean)^2, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)) / sqrt(sum(Const_Population)),
            Const_Expectation_SE = sqrt(sum(Const_Population * (Expectation - Const_Expectation_mean)^2, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)) / sqrt(sum(Const_Population))
        ) %>%
        ungroup()
    
    return(const_block)
}

Aggregate from constituencies to provinces. We weigh both the means and the standard errors by population. Process is repeated for the countrywide estimates.

aggregate_to_district <- function(const_data) {
    district_data <- const_data %>%
        select(-Const) %>%
        group_by(District, DecadeMarried) %>%
        summarise(
            District_Adjusted_mean = sum(Const_Adjusted_mean * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population),
            District_Observed_mean = sum(Const_Observed_mean * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population),
            District_Expectation_mean = sum(Const_Expectation_mean * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population),
            District_Adjusted_SE = sqrt(sum((Const_Adjusted_SE^2) * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)),
            District_Observed_SE = sqrt(sum((Const_Observed_SE^2) * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)),
            District_Expectation_SE = sqrt(sum((Const_Expectation_SE^2) * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)),
            District_Population = sum(Const_Population)
        ) %>%
        ungroup()
    return(district_data)
}
aggregate_to_province <- function(const_data) {
    province_data <- const_data %>%
        select(-Const, -District) %>%
        group_by(Province, DecadeMarried) %>%
        summarise(
            Province_Adjusted_mean = sum(Const_Adjusted_mean * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population),
            Province_Observed_mean = sum(Const_Observed_mean * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population),
            Province_Expectation_mean = sum(Const_Expectation_mean * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population),
            Province_Adjusted_SE = sqrt(sum((Const_Adjusted_SE^2) * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)),
            Province_Observed_SE = sqrt(sum((Const_Observed_SE^2) * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)),
            Province_Expectation_SE = sqrt(sum((Const_Expectation_SE^2) * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)),
            Province_Population = sum(Const_Population)
        ) %>%
        ungroup()
    return(province_data)
}

aggregate_to_national <- function(const_data) {
    national_data <- const_data %>%
        group_by(DecadeMarried) %>%
        summarise(
            National_Adjusted_mean = sum(Const_Adjusted_mean * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population),
            National_Observed_mean = sum(Const_Observed_mean * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population),
            National_Expectation_mean = sum(Const_Expectation_mean * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population),
            National_Adjusted_SE = sqrt(sum((Const_Adjusted_SE^2) * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)),
            National_Observed_SE = sqrt(sum((Const_Observed_SE^2) * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)),
            National_Expectation_SE = sqrt(sum((Const_Expectation_SE^2) * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)),
            National_Population = sum(Const_Population)
        ) %>%
        ungroup()
    return(national_data)
}

Drop the information about decade married and aggregate, likewise using weighted mean and standard errors.

calculate_overall_national <- function(const_data) {
    national_summary <- const_data %>%
        summarise(
            Total_National_Adjusted_mean = sum(Const_Adjusted_mean * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population),
            Total_National_Observed_mean = sum(Const_Observed_mean * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population),
            Total_National_Expectation_mean = sum(Const_Expectation_mean * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population),
            Total_National_Adjusted_SE = sqrt(sum((Const_Adjusted_SE^2) * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)),
            Total_National_Observed_SE = sqrt(sum((Const_Observed_SE^2) * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)),
            Total_National_Expectation_SE = sqrt(sum((Const_Expectation_SE^2) * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)),
            Total_National_Population = sum(Const_Population)
        ) %>%
        ungroup()
    return(national_summary)
}

calculate_overall_province <- function(const_data) {
    province_summary <- const_data %>%
        group_by(Province) %>%
        summarise(
            Total_Province_Adjusted_mean = sum(Const_Adjusted_mean * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population),
            Total_Province_Observed_mean = sum(Const_Observed_mean * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population),
            Total_Province_Expectation_mean = sum(Const_Expectation_mean * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population),
            Total_Province_Adjusted_SE = sqrt(sum((Const_Adjusted_SE^2) * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)),
            Total_Province_Observed_SE = sqrt(sum((Const_Observed_SE^2) * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)),
            Total_Province_Expectation_SE = sqrt(sum((Const_Expectation_SE^2) * Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)),
            Total_Province_Population = sum(Const_Population)
        ) %>% ungroup()
    return(province_summary)
}

Connect functions together.

calculate_results <- function(data) {
    const_ethnic <- process_constituency_ethnic(data)
    const_block <- process_constituency_block(data)
    
    provincial_ethnic <- aggregate_to_province(const_ethnic)
    provincial_block <- aggregate_to_province(const_block)
    
    national_ethnic <- aggregate_to_national(const_ethnic)
    national_block <- aggregate_to_national(const_block)
    
    total_national_ethnic <- calculate_overall_national(const_ethnic) %>%
        mutate(Level = "Total National Ethnic")
    
    total_national_block <- calculate_overall_national(const_block) %>%
        mutate(Level = "Total National Block")
    
    overall_province_ethnic <- calculate_overall_province(const_ethnic) %>%
        mutate(Level = "Total Province Ethnic")
    
    overall_province_block <- calculate_overall_province(const_block) %>%
        mutate(Level = "Total Province Block")

    list(
        decennial_national_ethnic = national_ethnic,
        decennial_national_block = national_block,
        decennial_province_ethnic = provincial_ethnic,
        decennial_province_block = provincial_block,
        total_national_ethnic = total_national_ethnic,
        total_national_block = total_national_block,
        overall_province_ethnic = overall_province_ethnic,
        overall_province_block = overall_province_block
    )
}

Run iterations of the function for every sample we are interested in.

run_filters <- function(data) {
    filters <- list(
        "Full Sample" = data,
        "Urban (>= 0.5)" = data %>% filter(Urbanization >= 0.5),
        "Urban (>= 0.75)" = data %>% filter(Urbanization >= 0.75),
        "Urban (>= 0.85)" = data %>% filter(Urbanization >= 0.85),
        "Rural (< 0.5)" = data %>% filter(Urbanization < 0.5),
        "Rural (< 0.75)" = data %>% filter(Urbanization < 0.75),
        "Rural (< 0.85)" = data %>% filter(Urbanization < 0.85)
    )
    
    results_dfs <- list()

    for (filter_name in names(filters)) {
        filtered_data <- filters[[filter_name]]
        result <- calculate_results(filtered_data)
        
        results_dfs[[paste0(filter_name, "_decennial_national_ethnic")]] <- result$decennial_national_ethnic
        results_dfs[[paste0(filter_name, "_decennial_national_block")]] <- result$decennial_national_block
        results_dfs[[paste0(filter_name, "_decennial_province_ethnic")]] <- result$decennial_province_ethnic
        results_dfs[[paste0(filter_name, "_decennial_province_block")]] <- result$decennial_province_block
        results_dfs[[paste0(filter_name, "_total_national_ethnic")]] <- result$total_national_ethnic
        results_dfs[[paste0(filter_name, "_total_national_block")]] <- result$total_national_block
        results_dfs[[paste0(filter_name, "_total_province_ethnic")]] <- result$overall_province_ethnic
        results_dfs[[paste0(filter_name, "_total_province_block")]] <- result$overall_province_block
    }
    
    results_dfs
}

process_constituency_ethnic <- function(data) {
    const_intermarriage_ethnic <- data %>%
        mutate(Urbanization_Group = cut(Urbanization, breaks = seq(0, 1, by = 0.1), labels = seq(0.1, 1, by = 0.1), include.lowest = TRUE)) %>%
        select(Const, Ethnicity, EthnicOutmarriage, Urbanization_Group) %>%
        left_join(y = ethnic_proportions, by = join_by(Const, Ethnicity)) %>%
        group_by(Const, Ethnicity, Proportion, Urbanization_Group) %>%
        reframe(Observed = mean(EthnicOutmarriage), n = n()) %>%
        mutate(Expectation = 1 - Proportion) %>%
        mutate(Adjusted = Observed / Expectation) %>%
        ungroup()

    const_ethnic <- const_intermarriage_ethnic %>%
        na.omit() %>%
        group_by(Urbanization_Group) %>%
        summarise(
            Const_Population = sum(n),
            Const_Adjusted_mean = sum(Adjusted * Proportion) / sum(Proportion, na.rm = TRUE),
            Const_Observed_mean = sum(Observed * Proportion) / sum(Proportion, na.rm = TRUE),
            Const_Expectation_mean = sum(Expectation * Proportion) / sum(Proportion, na.rm = TRUE),
            Const_Adjusted_SE = sqrt(sum(Const_Population * (Adjusted - Const_Adjusted_mean)^2, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)) / sqrt(sum(Const_Population)),
            Const_Observed_SE = sqrt(sum(Const_Population * (Observed - Const_Observed_mean)^2, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)) / sqrt(sum(Const_Population)),
            Const_Expectation_SE = sqrt(sum(Const_Population * (Expectation - Const_Expectation_mean)^2, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)) / sqrt(sum(Const_Population))
        ) %>%
        ungroup()
    
    return(const_ethnic)
}

process_constituency_block <- function(data) {
    const_intermarriage_block <- data %>%
        mutate(Urbanization_Group = cut(Urbanization, breaks = seq(0, 1, by = 0.1), labels = seq(0.1, 1, by = 0.1), include.lowest = TRUE)) %>%
        select(Const, EthnicBlock, BlockOutmarriage, Urbanization_Group) %>%
        left_join(y = ethnic_block_proportions, by = join_by(Const, EthnicBlock)) %>%
        group_by(Const, EthnicBlock, Proportion, Urbanization_Group) %>%
        reframe(Observed = mean(BlockOutmarriage), n = n()) %>%
        mutate(Expectation = 1 - Proportion) %>%
        mutate(Adjusted = Observed / Expectation) %>%
        ungroup()

    const_block <- const_intermarriage_block %>%
        group_by(Urbanization_Group) %>%
        summarise(
            Const_Population = sum(n),
            Const_Adjusted_mean = sum(Adjusted * Proportion) / sum(Proportion, na.rm = TRUE),
            Const_Observed_mean = sum(Observed * Proportion) / sum(Proportion, na.rm = TRUE),
            Const_Expectation_mean = sum(Expectation * Proportion) / sum(Proportion, na.rm = TRUE),
            Const_Adjusted_SE = sqrt(sum(Const_Population * (Adjusted - Const_Adjusted_mean)^2, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)) / sqrt(sum(Const_Population)),
            Const_Observed_SE = sqrt(sum(Const_Population * (Observed - Const_Observed_mean)^2, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)) / sqrt(sum(Const_Population)),
            Const_Expectation_SE = sqrt(sum(Const_Population * (Expectation - Const_Expectation_mean)^2, na.rm = TRUE) / sum(Const_Population)) / sqrt(sum(Const_Population))
        ) %>%
        ungroup()
    
    return(const_block)
}
